results.name: Self-inverse and multiplicative permutation of natural numbers, A091202-conjugate of Blue code: a(n) = A091203(A193231(A091202(n))).
comment: a(n) has the same prime signature as n: the permutation maps primes to primes, squares to squares, cubes to cubes, and so on.
link: Antti Karttunen, Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..8191
Index entries for sequences that are permutations of the natural numbers
formula: Completely multiplicative with p_i = p_{A234751(i)} (where p_i stands for the i-th prime, A000040(i)), and a(x*y) = a(x)*a(y) for x, y > 0.
results.author: _Antti Karttunen_, Dec 31 2013
